# Project Architecture Rules

This repository layout:

```txt
project-root/
├── backend/     # Java Spring Boot
├── mobile/      # Flutter Dart
└── README.md
```

## Backend architecture (current)

Backend uses package-by-feature under `com.taxiincome`:

- `common/` — cross-cutting concerns (filters, config, utilities, exception handling)
- `user/`, `order/`, `dashboard/`, `schedule/` — domain modules

Rules:

- Controllers should stay thin: mapping + validation + delegating to services.
- Services own business rules and orchestration.
- Repositories own persistence queries.
- Entities map DB tables.
- DTO records are used for API input/output.

Do not force a different folder taxonomy (like `controller/service/impl`) unless explicitly requested.

## Mobile architecture (current)

Flutter app uses:

- `mobile/lib/core/` — theme, networking, storage, providers
- `mobile/lib/features/<feature>/` — screens + repositories + models
- `mobile/lib/widgets/` — reusable UI widgets

Rules:

- Prefer feature folders matching backend domains when possible.
- UI should not embed HTTP details; keep HTTP in repositories / `ApiClient`.
- Keep widgets small; avoid huge `build()` methods.

## Shared rules

- Backend and mobile must agree on API contract.
- Never change response JSON shape without updating mobile parsing.
- Never change mobile model fields without checking backend DTOs.
- Prefer consistent naming between backend DTO fields and mobile `fromJson` keys.
